#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.33"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.33:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.33:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga "
msgstr "4. Situations "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.33:0.3"
msgid "33. Sīhasutta "
msgstr "33. The Lion "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.33, sc1
msgctxt "an4.33:1.1"
msgid "“Sīho, bhikkhave, migarājā sāyanhasamayaṃ āsayā nikkhamati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, towards evening the lion, king of beasts, emerges from his den, "

msgctxt "an4.33:1.2"
msgid "Āsayā nikkhamitvā vijambhati. "
msgstr "yawns, "

msgctxt "an4.33:1.3"
msgid "Vijambhitvā samantā catuddisā anuviloketi. "
msgstr "looks all around the four directions, "

msgctxt "an4.33:1.4"
msgid "Samantā catuddisā anuviloketvā tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ nadati. "
msgstr "and roars his lion’s roar three times. "

msgctxt "an4.33:1.5"
msgid "Tikkhattuṃ sīhanādaṃ naditvā gocarāya pakkamati. "
msgstr "Then he sets out on the hunt. "

msgctxt "an4.33:1.6"
msgid "Ye kho pana te, bhikkhave, tiracchānagatā pāṇā sīhassa migarañño nadato saddaṃ suṇanti, te yebhuyyena bhayaṃ saṃvegaṃ santāsaṃ āpajjanti. "
msgstr "And the animals who hear the roar of the lion, king of beasts, are typically filled with fear, awe, and terror. "

#. VAR: dakaṃ dakāsayā → udakaṃ udakāsayā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an4.33:1.7"
msgid "Bilaṃ bilāsayā pavisanti, dakaṃ dakāsayā pavisanti, vanaṃ vanāsayā pavisanti, ākāsaṃ pakkhino bhajanti. "
msgstr "They return to their lairs, be they in a hole, the water, or a wood; and the birds take to the air. "

msgctxt "an4.33:1.8"
msgid "Yepi te, bhikkhave, rañño nāgā gāmanigamarājadhānīsu daḷhehi varattehi bandhanehi baddhā, tepi tāni bandhanāni sañchinditvā sampadāletvā bhītā muttakarīsaṃ cajamānā yena vā tena vā palāyanti. "
msgstr "Even the royal elephants, bound with strong harnesses in the villages, towns, and capital cities, break apart their bonds, and urinate and defecate in terror as they flee here and there. "

# NOTE: The same phrase is used of Baka Brahma in MN 49, where the sense is not to extol his power, but to limit it. Hence the idiom itself is neutral, not: “So powerful … “but” That is how powerful …”
msgctxt "an4.33:1.9"
msgid "Evaṃ mahiddhiko kho, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā tiracchānagatānaṃ pāṇānaṃ, evaṃ mahesakkho evaṃ mahānubhāvo. "
msgstr "That’s how powerful is the lion, king of beasts, among animals, how illustrious and mighty. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.33:2.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yadā tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā, so dhammaṃ deseti: "
msgstr "In the same way, when a Realized One arises in the world—perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed—he teaches the Dhamma: "

#. VAR: sakkāyanirodho → sakkāyassa nirodho (s1-3) | sakkāyassa atthaṅgamo (aṭṭha.)
msgctxt "an4.33:2.2"
msgid "‘iti sakkāyo, iti sakkāyasamudayo, iti sakkāyanirodho, iti sakkāyanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Such is identity, such is the origin of identity, such is the cessation of identity, such is the practice that leads to the cessation of identity.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.33:2.3"
msgid "Yepi te, bhikkhave, devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā uccesu vimānesu ciraṭṭhitikā, tepi tathāgatassa dhammadesanaṃ sutvā yebhuyyena bhayaṃ saṃvegaṃ santāsaṃ āpajjanti: "
msgstr "Now, there are gods who are long-lived, beautiful, and very happy, lasting long in their divine palaces. When they hear this teaching by the Realized One, they’re typically filled with fear, awe, and terror. "

msgctxt "an4.33:2.4"
msgid "‘aniccā vata kira, bho, mayaṃ samānā niccamhāti amaññimha; "
msgstr "‘Oh no! It turns out we’re impermanent, though we thought we were permanent! "

msgctxt "an4.33:2.5"
msgid "addhuvā vata kira, bho, mayaṃ samānā dhuvamhāti amaññimha; "
msgstr "It turns out we don’t last, though we thought we were everlasting! "

msgctxt "an4.33:2.6"
msgid "asassatā vata kira, bho, mayaṃ samānā sassatamhāti amaññimha. "
msgstr "It turns out we’re transient, though we thought we were eternal! "

msgctxt "an4.33:2.7"
msgid "Mayaṃ kira, bho, aniccā addhuvā asassatā sakkāyapariyāpannā’ti. "
msgstr "It turns out that we’re impermanent, not lasting, transient, and included within identity.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.33:2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ mahiddhiko kho, bhikkhave, tathāgato sadevakassa lokassa, evaṃ mahesakkho evaṃ mahānubhāvoti. "
msgstr "That’s how powerful is the Realized One in the world with its gods, how illustrious and mighty. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.34, sc3
msgctxt "an4.33:3.1"
msgid "Yadā buddho abhiññāya, "
msgstr "The Buddha, the teacher without a peer "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:3.2"
msgid "dhammacakkaṃ pavattayī; "
msgstr "in all the world with its gods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:3.3"
msgid "Sadevakassa lokassa, "
msgstr "rolls forth the Wheel of Dhamma "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:3.4"
msgid "satthā appaṭipuggalo. "
msgstr "from his own insight: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.33:4.1"
msgid "Sakkāyañca nirodhañca, "
msgstr "identity, its cessation, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:4.2"
msgid "sakkāyassa ca sambhavaṃ; "
msgstr "the origin of identity, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:4.3"
msgid "Ariyañcaṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ, "
msgstr "and the noble eightfold path "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:4.4"
msgid "dukkhūpasamagāminaṃ. "
msgstr "that leads to the stilling of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.33:5.1"
msgid "Yepi dīghāyukā devā, "
msgstr "And then the long-lived gods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:5.2"
msgid "vaṇṇavanto yasassino; "
msgstr "so beautiful and famous, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:5.3"
msgid "Bhītā santāsamāpāduṃ, "
msgstr "are afraid and full of terror, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:5.4"
msgid "sīhassevitare migā. "
msgstr "like the other beasts when they hear a lion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.33:6.1"
msgid "Avītivattā sakkāyaṃ, "
msgstr "‘We haven’t transcended identity! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:6.2"
msgid "aniccā kira bho mayaṃ; "
msgstr "It turns out we’re impermanent!’ "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:6.3"
msgid "Sutvā arahato vākyaṃ, "
msgstr "So they say when they hear the word "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.33:6.4"
msgid "vippamuttassa tādino”ti. "
msgstr "of the perfected one, free and poised.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.33:6.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
